I solved the problem building my own extension of `ElasticsearchVectorStore`, with this modification, and a new `toDocument` to convert between those documents. It is working correctly as expected, reading and writing (id, content)

```
	private Document toDocument(Hit<ElasticSearchDocument> hit) {

		ElasticSearchDocument doc = hit.source();

		Document.Builder documentBuilder = Document.builder()
				.id(doc.id())
				.text(doc.content())
				.metadata(doc.metadata());

		//media does not exist ElasticSearchDocument !
		/*
		if (doc.media() != null && !doc.media().isEmpty()) {
			documentBuilder.media(doc.media.get(0));
		}
		*/

		if (hit.score() != null) {
			documentBuilder.metadata(DocumentMetadata.DISTANCE.value(), 1 - normalizeSimilarityScore(hit.score()));
			documentBuilder.score(normalizeSimilarityScore(hit.score()));
		}
		return documentBuilder.build();
	}
````

Therefore,
- Altough I used an extension, this change has to be made in the ElasticsearchVectorStore
- The extension of the store is very hard and cumbersome because a lot of methods are private and not protected wich requires too many copies on the subclasss (eg normalizeSimilarityScore) (why not protected as default ???)

**Notes**: 
- The problem was not in media, but in the change from context to text
- The media does not exist in ElasticSearchDocument, I don´t know if its relevant to have and consider in the toDocument method. I was using some code for that because I was using first my own version of ESDocument and my store had the media field stored as an array (but in fact empty)

@dev-jonghoonpark ,

I noticed that in your last commit you removed ElasticSearchDocument in order to manipulate the fields as a map to change the embedding field name. That will make the toDocument harder to implment. I did that at first : use Object as the parameterized type in the search, and then toDocument receives a map of values, but the the solution is not strongly typed and its based on strings :-(

So I think the ElasticSearchDocument should be reintroduced (at least only for reading), if the configurable name for embeddings field cannot be solved by any Spring technique (like a dynamic json annotation or mixin) or in the Jackson mapper.

